=> Ussualy the Unit test will work on a separate file.
=> Naming Conventions:
    - circles.py / test_circles.py (Name of the unit test)
    - circles.py / circles_test.py (Name of the unit test)

=> To have a unit test need to import import unittest, and to create a class as:
    - class NameOfTheClass(unitttest.TestCase):

=> To run a unit test on the shell, use:
    - python -m unittest name_of_the_test
        - ex: python -m unittest test_circles
    - "-m" instructs python to run the unit test module as a script

    - Another way to run unit test is:
        - python -m unittest
        - Python will automatically search for tests and run them